RACE.FOOTNOTES: SCRUPULOUS bumped with an outer rival at the start, tracked along the inside, tipped out and took aim outside of the embattled leading pair in upper stretch, ranged up to them in the final furlong, drove past nearing the sixteenth pole and drew clear. END OF INNOCENCE broke outwardly, advanced to prompt the pace three wide, then two wide into the turn, bid and vied around the bend, sustained the duel through midstretch, but was outkicked by an outer rival with a sixteenth to go and edged his inner counterpart for place. WHATTA WORLD bumped with an inner rival upon leaving the gates, showed the way along the inside, sparred with an outer bidder around the turn, gamely clung to an advantage through midstretch, but yielded to his outer counterpart and a wider bidder at the sixteenth pole. INTERCEPTION prompted the pace two wide and between horses for a quarter mile, backed of between the top pair to stalk them nearing the turn, got coaxed along turning for home before spinning for home three wide, but hung on his left lead thereafter and lacked a bid. BETTE DAVIS leaned inwardly while off a step slow, bobbled moments after the start before the rider took a hard hold to keep from hitting the inner rail, trailed in the aftermath, moved out of last two to three wide nearing the lane and stayed on. NO VIOLENCE lacked a response to urging while off of the pace in the two to three path around the turn, yet improved between horses in the final furlong. LOVEYA LOVEYA MORE chased from midpack in the three to two path around the turn and weakened. HUSH IT HONEY tracked three wide, then weakened in the four path in upper stretch. SUMMER DANCE was off a step slow, lacked speed along the inside and faded.

FLOORED transferred contact from an inner rival to outer foes leaving the chute, stalked the leading trio from the two path, tipped outside of them in upper stretch, lacked true progress in pursuit of the embattled leading pair through midstretch, yet kicked in once an outer WEST OMAHA rallied alongside in the final furlong, surged late along with that foe and narrowly prevailed over her in the place photo while gaining on the leader. MUGEN prompted the pace three wide, vied turning for home, sparred with an inner CANDY LANDY in upper stretch, wrestled a narrow advantage with exchanging a shoulder-to-shoulder brush with that one at the three sixteenths pole, but relinquished the advantage to his inner counterpart at the furlong grounds, failed to keep pace in the final sixteenth and was surpassed by a pair of outer rivals nearing the wire. CLASS ACT was void of speed, raced far back in the three path before fanning seven wide entering the lane, failed to match rallying strides with an inner rival moving to midstretch, yet stayed on for a minor share. AUSTIN TRAFFIC got bumped between horses and steadied in crowded quarters at the thirteen sixteenths pole, pursued from midpack along the inside and chased evenly. FUNDAMENTALLY tracked four wide, came under coaxing at the three furlong pole, floated five wide into the lane and gave way between horses. CONTROLLED TEMPER vied for the lead two wide and between rivals, but folded in upper stretch. LITTLE MISS PRISS laid off of the pace in the three path, moved between horses leaving the three furlong pole, and weakened. BABE IN THE WOODS got pinched between horses inside the thirteen sixteenths pole, lost her rider exiting the chute and was vanned off.
